casebody.data:
Monday, October 7, 1991

MOTION DOCKET

91-1750. Newbold v. Keller.

In Prohibition or Mandamus. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of prohibition, or in the alternative, a writ of mandamus. Upon consideration of respondents’ motion for protective order,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said motion for protective order be, and the same is hereby, denied, effective October 4, 1991.
